  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math alttext=\"one fourth\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>. For an equation in slope-intercept form <math alttext=\"y equals m x plus b\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>, <math alttext=\"m\"><mi>m</mi>\n</math> represents the slope of the line in the <em>xy</em>-plane defined by this equation. It's given that line&nbsp;<math alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math> is defined by <math alttext=\"3 y plus 12 x equals 5\"><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>. Subtracting <math alttext=\"12 x\"><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi></math> from both sides of this equation yields <math alttext=\"3 y equals minus 12 x plus 5\"><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></math>. Dividing both sides of this equation by <math alttext=\"3\"><mn>3</mn>\n</math> yields <math alttext=\"y equals minus StartFraction 12 Over 3 EndFraction x plus five thirds\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>, or <math alttext=\"y equals minus 4 x plus five thirds\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>. Thus, the slope of line&nbsp;<math alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math> in the <em>xy</em>-plane is <math alttext=\"negative 4\"><mrow>\n<mo>-</mo>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Since line <math alttext=\"n\"><mi>n</mi>\n</math> is perpendicular to line <math alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math> in the <em>xy</em>-plane, the slope of line <math alttext=\"n\"><mi>n</mi>\n</math> is the negative reciprocal of the slope of line <math alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math>. The negative reciprocal of <math alttext=\"negative 4\"><mrow>\n<mo>-</mo>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math> is <math alttext=\"minus StartFraction 1 Over left parenthesis negative 4 right parenthesis EndFraction equals one fourth\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>. Note that 1/4 and .25 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer.</p>",
